    </script>

    <style>
        /* Base styling */
        body {
            background-color: #fdfbf7;
            color: #333;
            -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        }

        /* Chart Container Requirements */
        .chart-container {
            position: relative;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            height: 300px;
            max-height: 400px;
        }
        @media (min-width: 768px) {
            .chart-container {
                height: 350px;
            }
        }

        /* Custom Scrollbar */
        ::-webkit-scrollbar {
            width: 8px;
        }
        ::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
            background: #f7f3e8; 
        }
        ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
            background: #cbd5e1; 
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
            background: #94a3b8; 
        }

        /* Interactive Elements transitions */
        .route-btn {
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }
        .route-btn.active {
            background-color: #0369a1;
            color: white;
            transform: scale(1.02);
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 2px 4px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
        }
        .route-btn:not(.active):hover {
            background-color: #f1f5f9;
            transform: translateY(-2px);
        }
        
        /* Card hover effects */
        .info-card {
            transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
        }
        .info-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-4px);
            box-shadow: 0 10px 15px -3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-sand-50 font-sans text-stone-800">

    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals (Sand/Stone) as base to represent the landscape, Caspian Blue (sky/sea) for primary interactions, and Flame Orange for accents representing the Land of Fire. -->
    
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: 
         1. Header/Hero: Establishes context and tone.
         2. Overview & Preparations (Grid): Displays general driving rules and the trunk checklist side-by-side for quick reference before the trip.
         3. Interactive Route Explorer (Dashboard approach): The core feature. Users select a route via tabs. The view dynamically updates to show step-by-step directions, coordinates, and a breakdown chart of distances. This prevents information overload and lets the user focus on one day at a time.
         4. Mileage Analysis (Visualization): A comparative view showing total distances per day, helping the family understand which days are driving-heavy vs rest-heavy.
    -->
    
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
         - Driving Rules/Checklist -> Goal: Inform -> UI Cards with Unicode icons -> Justification: Easy to scan, distinct visual blocks.
         - Route Specifics -> Goal: Organize/Interact -> Tabbed Dashboard + Dynamic List -> Justification: Keeps UI clean. Users only see details for the day they care about.
         - Daily Segment Breakdown -> Goal: Compare -> Doughnut Chart (Chart.js) -> Justification: Visually shows which part of the day's drive is the longest. NO SVG used.
         - Total Trip Mileage -> Goal: Compare/Analyze -> Bar Chart (Chart.js) -> Justification: Quickly reveals driving intensity across the 4 routes. NO SVG used.
    -->
    
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->

